Key Match Events: Ranger Suárez struck out the first five batters in his second start since missing a month with lower-back tightness.
Orlando Arcia hit his 14th homer of the year, and Sean Murphy connected for his eighth homer for a 2-0 lead.
Arcia homered again to a rousing chorus of boos in the sixth off reliever Max Lazar for a 5-0 lead.
Atlanta Braves hit at least three home runs in a game for the 26th time this season, the most in the National League.
Others: The Phillies' No. 1 and No. 2 hitters, Kyle Schwarber and Trea Turner, were a combined 0-for-8.
Phillies reliever José Alvarado returned to the team after being placed on the restricted list for a personal matter.
All-Star third baseman Alec Bohm did not play due to a left hand injury.
